Zanzibar government has suspended its marine transport and other seafaring activities starting from Saturday at 9 am until further notice. The decision was announced by the Minister of State in the Office of Second Vice President; Dr Khalid Salum Mohammed saying that the government has decided to take precautions against the hurricane which is heading to the Tanzaniaâ€™s coast. The Tanzania Meteorological Authority (TMA) statement issued Saturday stated that the hurricane is located 200 kilometers from the Mafia Island and traveling at a speed of 18 kilometers per hour.